Taught by Prof Christopher Brooks from University of Michigan (Offered through Coursera)
Programming software: Python
Package: Pandas, Numpy, Matplotlib, Seaborn
Completed on 27 Jun 20

Module 1
  - Principles of data visualization.
  - Alberto Cairo's work, Graphics Lies, Misleading Visuals

Module 2
  - Basic charting
  - Use CSV weather data and produce a composite chart
  
Module 3
  - Charting fundamentals
  - Visualization technique to convert a static image to an interactive chart

Module 4
  - Identify publicly accessible datasets and create a visual chart by using Matplotlib.

